This formula calculates the total ion intensity for each sample s, summing to Ns. This approach enables the determination of the coefficient of variation (CV) for the ion count of each lipid in a sample (yls). The dispersion (Φl) of each lipid and is calculated using the common dispersion method5. On the basis of these values, the log2 fold change (log2FC) between samples is calculated, and the corresponding P values are derived using the likelihood ratio test. P values less than 0.05 were considered significant. Microglia lipidomics data are available online at https://github.com/chopralab/Lesion-remote_astrocytes_govern_microglia-mediated_white_matter_repair.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
